// tree.utils
// Utility functions for building, sorting, and filtering the nested file tree used by PseudoFileTree.
// synced: 2026-03-26T00:00:00Z

Type exported: TreeNode { name, path, children, isDir }.

FUNCTION buildTree(fileList) -> TreeNode[] [2026-03-26]                EXPORT
  Converts a flat list of slash-delimited file paths into a nested TreeNode hierarchy.
  FOR each filePath, split on "/" and walk the levels. At each level create a node keyed by segment name if it does not exist, using a temporary _childrenMap object for O(1) child lookup.
  After processing all paths, convert every _childrenMap back to a children array via convertChildrenMap and RETURN the root nodes as an array.

---

FUNCTION convertChildrenMap(node) -> TreeNode
  Recursive helper. IF the node has a _childrenMap, replace children with Object.values of that map, each recursively converted. Delete _childrenMap. RETURN the cleaned node.

---

FUNCTION deepSortTree(nodes) -> TreeNode[] [2026-03-26]                EXPORT
  Recursively sorts a tree so directories appear before files, with alphabetical ordering within each group.
  Calls sortTreeNodes for the current level, then maps each node to a copy with its children also deep-sorted.

---

FUNCTION sortTreeNodes(nodes) -> TreeNode[]
  Internal sort comparator wrapper. Sorts so isDir nodes come first; within the same type, sorts by localeCompare on name.

---

FUNCTION filterTree(nodes, query, ancestorMatched) -> { nodes, expandedPaths } [2026-03-26]                EXPORT
  Recursively filters a tree to nodes whose name matches the query string (case-insensitive) or whose ancestor matched.
  FOR each node, checks nameMatches and recurses into children. A node is included IF its name matches, an ancestor matched, OR any child was retained. Directories containing matches are added to expandedPaths so the caller can auto-expand them.
  RETURN the filtered node list and the set of paths that should be expanded.
